            answer: "Phenolphthalein is suitable because its colour change range (8.2вҖ“10.0) encompasses the equivalence point pH (8.72). Methyl orange is unsuitable because it changes colour at pH 3.1вҖ“4.4, far below the equivalence point вҖ” it would give a false end point.",
            commonError: "Assuming either indicator works for any titration. Indicator selection always depends on whether the indicator's pKa (and colour change range) coincides with the sharp vertical section of the titration curve at the equivalence point."
