                problem: "The Haber process operates at 450В°C and 200 atm with an iron catalyst, giving approximately 15% yield of NHвӮғ per pass. (a) Explain why a lower temperature would increase yield but is not used commercially. (b) Explain why an even higher pressure would increase yield but is not used commercially. (c) Explain the role of the iron catalyst in terms of activation energy and equilibrium position.",
