                        working: "The forward reaction is exothermic (О”H = вҲ’92 kJ molвҒ»В№). Lower temperature shifts equilibrium RIGHT (Le Chatelier: system moves in exothermic direction to compensate for heat removal), increasing Kc and NHвӮғ yield. However, lower temperature means fewer molecules have kinetic energy exceeding the activation energy (Arrhenius equation: k = Ae^(вҲ’Ea/RT)). Rate falls exponentially with decreasing temperature. At, say, 150В°C, Kc would be very large and yield would exceed 90%, but the reaction would be too slow to produce NHвӮғ commercially. 450В°C is the lowest temperature at which the iron catalyst gives a commercially viable rate.",
