        "Create a functional group properties comparison table. Rows: alkane, alcohol, halogenoalkane, aldehyde, ketone, carboxylic acid, ester, acyl chloride, amine, amide. Columns: (1) functional group structure; (2) characteristic reaction type; (3) one specific reagent for identification; (4) observation for a positive test. Fill every cell. This table is the foundation reference for all mechanism and identification questions.",
