        "Create a Ka and pKa comparison table for six common acids: HCl, HвӮӮSOвӮ„, HNOвӮғ (strong), then methanoic acid (Ka = 1.77 Г— 10вҒ»вҒҙ), ethanoic acid (Ka = 1.74 Г— 10вҒ»вҒө), carbonic acid KaвӮҒ (Ka = 4.3 Г— 10вҒ»вҒ·). Columns: (1) Ka; (2) pKa; (3) relative strength rank. Practise converting between Ka and pKa for each row until the conversion is automatic.",
