        "Particles in a liquid move faster than particles in a gas at the same temperature вҖ” FALSE: at the same temperature, gas particles have the same mean kinetic energy as liquid particles of the same mass; gas particles move more freely because intermolecular forces are negligible, but their mean speed is not necessarily higher",
        "Diffusion stops when equilibrium is reached вҖ” FALSE: random particle motion continues at equilibrium; the NET diffusion is zero (equal movement in all directions) but individual particles continue to move randomly"
