        "Evaporation cools a liquid because the liquid loses heat to the environment вҖ” FALSE: evaporation cools the liquid because the most energetic particles escape, reducing the mean kinetic energy of the remaining particles вҖ” it is an internal redistribution of energy, not heat loss to the environment"
