        "Absolute zero means the temperature cannot go any lower вҖ” TRUE in a theoretical sense but commonly misunderstood: absolute zero (0 K = вҲ’273В°C) is the theoretical temperature at which all particle motion ceases; it is unattainable in practice but scientists have cooled matter to within billionths of a degree of it",
