            "Algebraic method uses simultaneous equations вҖ” reliable for complex cases",
            "Net ionic equations cancel spectator ions to show the essential reaction",
            "Redox equations require charge balance in addition to atom balance",
            "Half-equation method: balance each half separately, then cancel electrons",
            "Polyatomic ions can be balanced as a unit if they appear unchanged",
            "Coefficients encode mole ratios вҖ” the basis for all stoichiometric calculations"
